---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Forecasts" description="Forecast publication framework for UK Elections, including uncertainty, backtests, and source snapshots.">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Forecasts</p>
    <h1>No naked probabilities.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Forecasts will only publish with model version, input snapshot, uncertainty, source notes,
      and a backtest record that survives later model changes.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="feature-list">
      <article>
        <h2>Intervals</h2>
        <p>Vote share and seat estimates need P10/P50/P90 or an equivalent interval format, not just a single headline number.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h2>Versioning</h2>
        <p>Every forecast output is tied to a model id, code revision, source snapshot, and publication timestamp.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h2>Backtests</h2>
        <p>Past predictions are immutable records used to report calibration, mean absolute error, and missed calls.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
